# React to Inertia.js with React Conversion Guide

## Overview

This guide covers migrating a standalone React SPA (with its own router and API calls) to a **Laravel + Inertia.js + React** stack. With Inertia, your React components become full-page "views" served by Laravel — no separate API needed for page data. The server renders the first HTML, Inertia handles subsequent client-side navigation.

## Tech Stack

- **Laravel**: 12.x
- **Inertia.js**: 3.x (server-side adapter: `inertiajs/inertia-laravel` ^3.0)
- **Inertia React adapter**: `@inertiajs/react` ^3.0
- **Optional**: `@inertiajs/vite` ^3.0 — page resolution and simplified SSR in dev ([client-side setup](https://inertiajs.com/docs/v3/installation/client-side-setup.md))
- **React**: 19.x (required by the v3 React adapter)
- **Tailwind CSS**: 4.x
- **Vite**: 6.x (via `laravel-vite-plugin`)

