## File Structure

### Standalone React SPA (Before)

```
src/
├── components/
│   ├── Navbar.jsx
│   └── ProductCard.jsx
├── pages/
│   ├── Home.jsx
│   ├── Products.jsx
│   └── ProductDetail.jsx
├── router.jsx          ← React Router
├── api/
│   └── products.js     ← fetch wrappers
└── main.jsx
```

### Laravel + Inertia + React (After)

```
app/
└── Http/Controllers/
    ├── HomeController.php
    ├── ProductController.php
    └── ...
resources/
└── js/
    ├── Pages/              ← Inertia page components (replaces src/pages/)
    │   ├── Home.jsx
    │   ├── Products/
    │   │   ├── Index.jsx
    │   │   └── Show.jsx
    │   └── Auth/
    │       └── Login.jsx
    ├── Components/         ← Reusable React components
    │   ├── Navbar.jsx
    │   └── ProductCard.jsx
    ├── Layouts/            ← Persistent layout wrappers
    │   └── AppLayout.jsx
    └── app.jsx             ← Inertia bootstrap (replaces main.jsx)
routes/
└── web.php                 ← All page routes (no API routes for page data)
```

### Vormia package dev sandbox (`dev/resources`)

This repository’s **dev** Inertia shell uses the same concepts as a host Laravel app, but pages live under a `vormia/` namespace and `resolve` maps `Inertia::render()` names to files on disk:

```
dev/resources/
├── views/
│   └── app.blade.php       ← @vite + <x-inertia::head /> + <x-inertia::app />
└── js/
    ├── app.tsx             ← createInertiaApp + import.meta.glob('./vormia/pages/**/*.tsx')
    ├── components/         ← Shared UI (e.g. shadcn-style primitives)
    │   └── ui/
    └── vormia/
        ├── layouts/        ← Optional persistent layouts for demo pages
        ├── pages/          ← Inertia pages (e.g. welcome.tsx, democrud/*.tsx)
        └── wayfinder/      ← Generated route/action helpers (optional)
```

`Inertia::render('welcome')` resolves to `vormia/pages/welcome.tsx`; `Inertia::render('democrud/index')` → `vormia/pages/democrud/index.tsx`. A host app using `resources/js/Pages/` is equally valid if `createInertiaApp` / `@inertiajs/vite` matches those paths.

### Root Blade template (Inertia v3)

You can use either style ([server-side setup](https://inertiajs.com/docs/v3/installation/server-side-setup.md)):

- **Classic directives**: `@vite(...)`, `@inertiaHead`, `@inertia` in `resources/views/app.blade.php`
- **v3 Blade components** (used in this package’s dev layout): `<x-inertia::head />` in `<head>` and `<x-inertia::app />` in `<body>`. The head component can wrap fallback `<title>` / meta for non-SSR output.

### Inertia v3 — features to know

See [Introduction](https://inertiajs.com/docs/v3/getting-started/index) and [Upgrade guide](https://inertiajs.com/docs/v3/getting-started/upgrade-guide.md) for the full list. Short list:

- **`useHttp`**: standalone HTTP requests without a full Inertia visit ([HTTP requests](https://inertiajs.com/docs/v3/the-basics/http-requests.md))
- **Optimistic updates** with automatic rollback on failure ([Optimistic updates](https://inertiajs.com/docs/v3/the-basics/optimistic-updates.md))
- **Layout props** via `useLayoutProps` for data shared between a persistent layout and pages ([Layouts](https://inertiajs.com/docs/v3/the-basics/layouts.md))
- **SSR**: with `@inertiajs/vite`, dev SSR can run alongside `npm run dev`; production still follows [SSR deployment](https://inertiajs.com/docs/v3/advanced/server-side-rendering.md)

