## State Management

### Local UI State — Still useState

Client-only state (modals, toggles, counters) works exactly the same:

```jsx
const [isOpen, setIsOpen] = useState(false);
```

### Server-Originated Data — Props, Not fetch()

Data that comes from the database arrives as page props. Never `fetch()` for initial page data.

```jsx
// ✅ Correct — data from Laravel controller via Inertia
export default function Show({ product, relatedProducts }) {
    return <div>{product.name}</div>;
}

// ❌ Avoid — unnecessary client fetch for page data
export default function Show({ productId }) {
    const [product, setProduct] = useState(null);
    useEffect(() => { fetch(`/api/products/${productId}`) ... }, []);
}
```

### Shared Data (Global Props) — usePage()

Data available across all pages (e.g., auth user, flash messages):

```php
// app/Http/Middleware/HandleInertiaRequests.php
public function share(Request $request): array
{
    return [
        ...parent::share($request),
        'auth' => [
            'user' => $request->user(),
        ],
        'flash' => [
            'success' => session('success'),
            'error'   => session('error'),
        ],
    ];
}
```

```jsx
// In any component
import { usePage } from '@inertiajs/react';

const { auth, flash } = usePage().props;
```

