## Data Fetching

### What Stays Client-Side

For data that changes without navigation (e.g., live search autocomplete), you can still use `fetch` or a library like TanStack Query for async client requests. But page-level data always comes from the controller.

```jsx
// Client-side fetch only for dynamic/partial data
const [suggestions, setSuggestions] = useState([]);

const search = async (term) => {
    const res = await fetch(`/api/search?q=${term}`);
    setSuggestions(await res.json());
};
```

For this case, define a separate API route:

```php
// routes/api.php
Route::get('/search', [SearchController::class, 'suggestions']);
```

