## Best Practices

1. **Page directory matches `resolve`** — Laravel convention is `resources/js/Pages/`; this package’s dev sandbox uses `resources/js/vormia/pages/`. `Inertia::render('Path/Name')` must map to a real module path.
2. **Never fetch page data client-side** — pass it from the controller as props
3. **Use `useForm` for all mutations** — it handles CSRF, redirects, and validation errors automatically
4. **Use persistent layouts** (render callback or `createInertiaApp` `defaultLayout`) so the shell does not remount on navigation — see [Layouts](https://inertiajs.com/docs/v3/the-basics/layouts.md) and the v3 layout caveat above
5. **Use Ziggy** for `route()` helper in JavaScript — avoids hardcoding URLs
6. **Use `router.reload({ only: [...] })`** for polling or partial refreshes instead of separate API calls; in v3 use **`router.cancelAll()`** instead of removed `router.cancel()` when cancelling visits ([manual visits](https://inertiajs.com/docs/v3/the-basics/manual-visits.md))
7. **TypeScript tip**: Define prop types with an interface matching the controller's returned array keys

